HEADWORD: Anteversion
<hw>An`te*ver"sion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>ante-</ets> + L. <ets>vertere</ets>, <ets>versum</ets>, to
turn.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A displacement of an organ, esp. of
the uterus, in such manner that its whole axis is directed further
forward than usual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antevert</ent>⟦br⟧
